{"TopicId":186180,"ForumId":35,"TopicTitle":"Lightweight mod installer [v1.0]","CreatedByName":"IronCretin","CreatedById":158162,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-08T17:31:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"IronCretin","CreatedById":158162,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-08T17:31:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you tired of installing mods manually by downloading endless zips from SpaceDock, hunting for their GameData folders, and dragging them into your KSP install? Do you also want to avoid the hassle of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E, or you want to use a custom or dev version of a mod? Then this tool is for you! This little command-line utility can pull mods from a variety of sources, including local and remote zip files, spacedock, and github.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/IronCretin/ksp-mod-installer/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGithub\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022unknown.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002216.82\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022761\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/206181796164009984/597820473996214274/unknown.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FCcFceu.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002244.36\u0022 height=\u0022417\u0022 width=\u0022940\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/FCcFceu.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022jmnUEKS.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002241.93\u0022 height=\u0022348\u0022 width=\u0022830\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/jmnUEKS.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nRequires Python 3.7 or later to run.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DanGSun","CreatedById":185092,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-04T13:57:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey, this is pretty cool, but can you add \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E-repo integration? For example to write smth like this:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Elwmi install ckan/telemachus-reborn -y\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhere lwmi is your installer, install is operation, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003Eckan\u003C/abbr\u003E/telemachus-reborn is id \u0026amp; -y is silent install flag.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}